    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae Trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/237">Heinricus</persName> divina clementia Romanorum
                        imperator augustus. Si circa sanctorum loca beneficia condigna impendimus,
                        hoc nostram imperialem maiestatem condecere credimus, insuper et aeterna
                        premia nos inde adipisci confidimus. Quapropter omnium Christi nostrorumque
                        fidelium universitatem scire volumus, qualiter nos per interventum dilectê
                        nostrê coniugis <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/365">Agnetis</persName>
                        et <persName key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops" ref="#people/2129"
                            >Herimanni</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/1850">Coloniensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> nostri scilicet <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> et Heinrici dilecti
                        cancellarii cêterorumque familiarium nostrorum <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >abbatiam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sanctê Mariê in
                                <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName></orgName> de
                        antecessore nostro imperatore <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7"
                            >Ottone</persName> a <persName key="#Archbishops"><name ref="Fredericus"
                                >Frederico</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1471"><placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Ravennatis </placeName>Ecclesiê</orgName> archiepiscopo iuxta
                        utriusque placitum ad imperialis subiectionem proprietatis concambitam, ac
                        postea ab <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130"
                            >Heinrico</persName> nostro altero antecessore corroboratam et ab
                            <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/3">Ugone</persName> marchione
                        magnifice ditatam et in nos successione imperii et legali iure hereditatam
                        et ad nostrê dominationis manus receptam cum omnibus suis pertinentiis,
                        quicquid videlicet predicta abbatia per aliquod munimen cartarum vel
                        traditionum detinet vel eidem pertinet ab <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1100">Ecclesia Romana</orgName> et Ravennate aut
                        ab aliqua alia, seu etiam quicquid iure proprietatis detinet aut acquirere
                        in futuro potuerit, id est totam <rs key="#Islands">insulam</rs> integram: a
                        primo latere <placeName ref="#places/4196">Pado</placeName> percurrente in
                            <rs key="#Sea">mare</rs>, secundo latere <rs key="#Shores">litus
                            maris</rs>, tertio latere <placeName ref="#places/3563"
                            >Gauro</placeName>; et <rs key="#Fisheries">piscaria</rs> quê vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Ports" ref="#estates/2465"><geogName key="#Fisheries"
                                ref="#estates/2457"><placeName key="#Fisheries #Ports"
                                    >Volana</placeName></geogName></geogName> cum <rs key="#Ports"
                            >portu</rs> integro, a <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Badarino</placeName> usque in
                        mare, et <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> quê dicitur <geogName key="#Massae"
                            ref="#estates/2454"><placeName key="#Massae" ref="#places/3559">Lacus
                                Sanctus</placeName></geogName> cum <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscaria</rs> quê vocatur <geogName key="#Fisheries"
                            ref="#estates/2455"><placeName>Tidini</placeName></geogName>, a primo
                        latere <rs key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> qui vocatur <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/3919">Grecolê</geogName> et fundo qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/2494"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                ref="#places/3520">Corna Cervina</placeName></geogName> et fluvio
                        qui vocatur <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3568">Cisi</placeName> et
                            <rs key="#Canals">canale</rs> qui vocatur <placeName key="#Canals"
                            ref="#places/3569">Curlo</placeName>, a secundo <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">valle</rs> quê vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos" ref="#places/4681">Farullê</placeName>
                        et fluvio qui vocatur <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3564">Conca
                            Agathê</placeName> descendente in Gaurum, a tertio latere ipso Gauro, a
                        quarto vero Pado percurrente; insuper <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> unam
                        integram quê vocatur <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2487"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes" ref="#places/4619">Hustolatus</placeName></geogName>
                        cum <rs key="#Plebs">plebe</rs> sua et aliam quê vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/3920"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                ref="#places/4695">Baoria</placeName></geogName> et curtem aliam quê
                        vocatur <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/3921"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                >Ultra canale</placeName></geogName>, cum omnibus ad monasterium
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1474">Sanctê Mariê
                            in Xenodochio</orgName> pertinentibus et cum omnibus quê predictê
                        abbatiê Ugo marchio filius <persName><name ref="Hubertus"
                            >Uberti</name></persName> dedit, quicquid etiam habet aut acquirere
                        potest infra Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646"
                            >Attesin</placeName> fluvium vel infra Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/3588">Sandalum</placeName> et quantacumque in apostolicê
                        sedis privilegio releguntur, verum etiam queque habet aut acquirere potest
                        in civitate Ravenna et infra totum <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2449">Comacliensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3538"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2435"
                            >Gavellensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/84"
                                >Ferrariensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/7"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2439"
                                >Bononiensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/38"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/208"
                                >Mutinensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2409"
                                >Corneliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3513"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2458"
                                >Faventinum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3515"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2459"
                                >Liviensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/4602"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2480"
                                >Pupiliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1479"
                                >Cesenatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                                ><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1478"
                                >Monteferetranum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1806"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1480">Ariminensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1807"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2482">Pensauriensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1808"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2481">Fanensem</geogName></placeName>
                        et <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1812"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2371">Urbinatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1803"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1481">Castellanum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/2752"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2462">Perusinum</geogName></placeName> et in omnibus
                        quoque locis, cum areis, edificiis, <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Churches">capellis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>,
                            <rs>salictis</rs>, <rs key="#Oil">olivetis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> , <rs>planitiebus</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >venationibus</rs> , <rs key="#Saltworks">salinis</rs> et cum omni
                        utilitate quê vel nominari vel scribi possit, ab omni subiectione
                        archiepiscoporum excutimus, ut regalis in perpetuum sit nullis dominantium
                        personis subiecta. Sint <rs key="#Monks">monachi</rs> eius ab omni secularis
                        servitii infestatione securi et ab omni angaria cum suis hominibus remoti;
                        qui de suis qualem voluerint abbatem eligant ab episcopo <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1498">Comacliensi</orgName> consecrandum, qui,
                        si sibi pro pecunia vel aliqua humana potestate molestus esse voluerit,
                        veniat ad archiepiscopum Ravennatem ab eo benedicendus, et si hoc in isto
                        quod in primo invenerit, ad qualemcumque episcopum voluerit causa
                        consecrationis properet. Si quis autem hoc preceptum fregerit, componat <rs
                            key="#Penalty">ducentas libras auri cocti</rs>, medietatem camerê nostrê
                        et medietatem prelibato monasterio. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc imperialem
                        paginam manu propria roboratam sigillari iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici
                        secundi Romanorum invictissimi imperatoris augusti. Heinricus cancellarius
                        vice Herimanni archicancellarii recognovi. Data V id. apr. anno dominicae
                        incarnationis MXLVII, indictione XV, anno autem domni Heinrici tercii
                        ordinationis eius XVIII, regnantis quidem VIII, secundi imperantis primo.
                        Actum Ravenne; in Dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
